\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy is the downstream operational partner of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 governs the authorization decision —
 whether a change may proceed and on what terms.
 This policy governs what happens after that authorization is granted:
 packaging,
 testing,
 and deploying the change to production.
 The Software Repository defined in Section 6.1 is the exclusive deployment source for all change categories.
 Category-specific deployment requirements are defined in Sections 6.4 through 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Software Repository
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Software Repository is the IT-controlled repository designated as the authoritative and exclusive source for all deployment packages within the scope of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure the Software Repository is read-only for all personnel except Information Operations Personnel with authorized write access.
 The IT Director shall establish and maintain the write-access authorization process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel shall refer to the Software Repository by its governance function label in all policy instruments.
 Server paths and share names shall not appear in policy text to preserve policy validity if the repository is relocated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Repository Eligibility
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Only applications,
 drivers,
 firmware,
 and associated documentation corresponding to items with a current Supported lifecycle status classification in the IT Asset Catalog maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 shall be present in the Software Repository and eligible for deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Presence in the repository without a corresponding Supported classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 constitutes a policy violation.
 The Assistant IT Director shall remediate any such condition upon discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director's approval of a Supported lifecycle status classification under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default

 is the intake authorization gate for repository eligibility.
 The Assistant IT Director shall prepare classification proposals and submit them to the IT Director for approval.
 No separate intake approval process is required under this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Repository Requirement —
 No Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel shall deploy exclusively from the Software Repository under all change categories,
 including Emergency.
 This requirement applies regardless of urgency,
 authorization status,
 or the identity of the personnel directing the deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Emergency category in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 authorizes expedited change authorization.
 It does not alter,
 waive,
 or supersede the deployment source requirement or the Supported classification eligibility requirement established in this policy.
 An Incident Commander's Emergency designation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 does not constitute authorization to deploy from an uncontrolled source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Standard Deployments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall deploy Standard changes from the Software Repository per the pre-approved Knowledge Base procedure maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Knowledge Base procedure is the deployment control for Standard changes;
 no staging or pilot group is required.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall document the deployment within the associated work order in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Service Request Fulfillment Policy).
 The CI update obligation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 applies upon completion of the deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Post-deployment verification for Standard deployments is implicit in work order closure under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Significant Deployments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall deploy Significant changes from the Software Repository.
 Before implementation,
 the deploying technician shall prepare and document a deployment package within the RFC record under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall complete staging or pilot group testing prior to full production deployment,
 in accordance with the testing requirements defined in Section 6.7.
 For Significant deployments affecting end-user systems,
 a phased rollout —
 pilot group before full production —
 shall be the default approach.
 Where a phased rollout is not applicable due to deployment scope or infrastructure constraints,
 the deploying technician shall document the basis for that determination in the RFC record before proceeding to full production deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall verify that the rollback procedure is operational before the deployment proceeds to production.
 The deploying technician shall document all deployment steps in the RFC record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Post-deployment verification is required before the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 PIR may be initiated.
 The Assistant IT Director shall confirm that post-deployment verification is complete and documented in the RFC record before the PIR is opened.
 The CI update obligation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 applies upon completion of the deployment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Emergency Deployments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The deploying technician shall deploy Emergency changes from the Software Repository.
 No exception to this requirement applies under Emergency conditions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

