\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Staging and Testing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall ensure that a dedicated test environment is maintained for pre-production validation of Significant deployments.
 The test environment shall consist of one (1) or more virtual machines representative of production system configurations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Where the dedicated test environment is not applicable to a specific deployment type —
 for example,
 infrastructure changes that cannot be meaningfully replicated in a virtual machine environment —
 the deploying technician shall use a defined pilot group as the validation mechanism and shall document the basis for test environment non-applicability in the RFC record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that the criteria for test environment applicability and pilot group selection are documented in the Knowledge Base under 
